IBADAN – The Commissioner of Police for Oyo State, CP. Ngozi Onadeko has called on media practitioners, to shun fake news in the interest of nation-building. CP. Onadeko made the call while receiving the leadership of the Nigeria Association of Women Journalists NAWOJ, Oyo state chapter, stressing that journalists must promote the unity of Nigeria, set an agenda that will help in the development of the country rather than publishing stories that can lead to chaos. CP Onadeko noted that the achievement recorded so far in the command, only became possible because she had hardworking officers who are up to the task of making the work successful. Group Laments High Rate Of Brutality Against  Journalists,… Let’s Work Together To Move Insurance Industry Forward –… She also noted that the officer in the command will continue to perform their duties professionally and as expected of them, assuring the public of the command’s commitment to the safety of lives and property. While speaking, the Chairperson of NAWOJ, Oyo State Chapter, comrade Jadesola Ajibola, recalled how the command under the leadership of CP Onadeko has been fighting Gender-Based Violence, worked assiduously through the collaboration of the public restored peace to the state. Comrade Ajibola noted that the command has been of good conduct and professional in human relations. POLL She said some of the cases NAWOJ has been following reflected that the Police under the leadership of the first female Commissioner of Police remain outstanding. The NAWOJ Chairperson assured the command of the association’s collaboration, towards the widows, professional reportage and investigative journalism. She added that widows in the command will benefit from some of the programs of NAWOJ, one way to make lives more meaningful for them.